HEADWORD: Pollack
<hw>Pol"lack</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G. & D.
<ets>pollack</ets>, and Gael. <ets>pollag</ets> a little pool, a sort of
fish.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A marine gadoid food
fish of Europe (<spn>Pollachius virens</spn>). Called also
<altname>greenfish</altname>, <altname>greenling</altname>,
<altname>lait</altname>, <altname>leet</altname>,
<altname>lob</altname>, <altname>lythe</altname>, and <altname>whiting
pollack</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The American pollock; the
coalfish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pollage</ent>⟦br⟧
